findia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fgerman-passenger-detained-for-inappropriately-intimate-act-on-swiss-air-flight%2Famp_articleshow%2F119606628.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Salman%20Rushdie%20To%20Publish%201st%20Fiction%20Book%20Since%20Brutal%20Stabbing%20In%202022%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBritish-American%20novelist%20Salman%20Rushdie%20will%20publish%20his%20first%20major%20work%20of%20fiction%20since%20the%20brutal%20stabbing%20that%20blinded%20him%20in%20one%20eye%2C%20his%20publisher%20said%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Eleventh%20Hour%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20collection%20of%20short%20stories%20examining%20themes%20and%20places%20of%20interest%20to%20Rushdie%2Cwho%20narrowly%20escaped%20death%20during%20the%202022%20attack.%20It%20will%20be%20released%20on%20November%204%2C%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20would-be%20assassin%2C%20Hadi%20Matar%2C%20was%20convicted%20of%20attempted%20murder%20at%20a%20trial%20in%20upstate%20New%20York%20at%20which%20Rushdie%20gave%20vivid%20testimony%20about%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20three%20novellas%20in%20this%20volume%2C%20all%20written%20in%20the%20last%20twelve%20months%2C%20explore%20themes%20and%20places%20that%20have%20been%20much%20on%20my%20mind%20--%20mortality%2C%20Bombay%2C%20farewells%2C%20England%20(especially%20Cambridge)%2C%20anger%2C%20peace%2C%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20released%20by%20Penguin%20publishing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20happy%20that%20the%20stories%2C%20very%20different%20from%20one%20another%20in%20setting%2C%20story%20and%20technique%2C%20nevertheless%20manage%20to%20be%20in%20conversation%20with%20one%20another%2C%20and%20with%20the%20two%20stories%20that%20serve%20as%20prologue%20and%20epilogue%20to%20this%20threesome.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20trial%20of%20Rushdie's%20attacker%2C%20Matar's%20legal%20team%20sought%20to%20prevent%20witnesses%20from%20characterizing%20Rushdie%20as%20a%20victim%20of%20persecution%20following%20Iran's%201989%20fatwa%20calling%20for%20his%20murder%20over%20supposed%20blasphemy%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Satanic%20Verses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERushdie%20told%20jurors%20of%20Matar%20%26quot%3Bstabbing%20and%20slashing%26quot%3B%20him%20during%20an%20event%20at%20an%20upscale%20cultural%20center%20in%20rural%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMatar%20was%20found%20guilty%20of%20stabbing%20Rushdie%20about%2010%20times%20with%20a%20six-inch%20blade%20that%20was%20shown%20to%20witnesses%20and%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20trial%2C%20Rushdie%20discussed%20his%20book%20%26quot%3BKnife%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20wrote%20after%20the%20attack%2C%20describing%20the%20violent%20attempt%20on%20his%20life%20and%20his%20recovery%20from%20a%20variety%20of%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defendant%20shouted%20pro-Palestinian%20slogans%20on%20several%20occasions%20during%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMatar%2C%20from%20New%20Jersey%2C%20previously%20told%20media%20he%20had%20only%20read%20two%20pages%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Satanic%20Verses%26quot%3B%20but%20believed%20the%20author%20had%20%26quot%3Battacked%20Islam.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20novel%20was%20published%20in%201988%2C%20Rushdie%20became%20the%20center%20of%20a%20fierce%20tug-of-war%20between%20free%20speech%20advocates%20and%20those%20who%20insisted%20that%20insulting%20religion%2C%20particularly%20Islam%2C%20was%20unacceptable%20in%20any%20circumstance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERushdie%2C%20who%20was%20born%20in%20Mumbai%20but%20moved%20to%20England%20as%20a%20boy%2C%20was%20propelled%20into%20the%20spotlight%20with%20his%20second%20novel%20%26quot%3BMidnight's%20Children%26quot%3B%20(1981)%2C%20which%20won%20Britain's%20prestigious%20Booker%20Prize%20for%20its%20portrayal%20of%20post-independence%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20%26quot%3BThe%20Satanic%20Verses%26quot%3B%20brought%20him%20far%20greater%2C%20mostly%2